This paper is about reinforcement learning algorithms, which are commonly studied in the machine learning and artificial intelligence communities. The paper specifically focuses on fixed-horizon temporal difference methods, which are a type of value function prediction algorithm. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.RO (Robotics). The paper also discusses convergence of the algorithms, which suggests it could be relevant to the cs.SY (Systems and Control) category. Finally, the use of function approximation techniques indicates that it could also be relevant to the cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) category.
